Sometimes a better alternative to a while-Loop is a for-Loop. This is the case when we know exactly how many steps we want to take! The syntax is as follows:
for (int i = 0; i < how many steps; i++) {
	<consequent>
}
For our purposes we need multiple for-Loops in succession:
for(int i = 0; i < 9; i++) {

for (int i = 0; i < 9; i++){
	<knight name>.move();
}
<knight name>.turn(RIGHT);
<knight name>.collect();
for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++){
	<knight name>.move();
}
...
